06:01.040 --> 06:03.680
which stands for intensive short-term dynamic psychotherapy,

06:04.000 --> 06:10.160
the type of therapy developed by Dr. Davenle in the 60s, I believe.

06:11.800 --> 06:15.200
And it's a very, yeah, we can get into the details of it.

06:15.200 --> 06:17.000
But essentially, it looks at

06:18.320 --> 06:20.960
it would look at chronic pain as being a defense

06:20.960 --> 06:23.520
against emotional experience.

06:23.520 --> 06:26.320
And so it's another way that we can avoid

06:26.760 --> 06:28.880
particularly painful emotional experience

06:28.880 --> 06:30.920
that our psyche, for whatever reason,

06:30.920 --> 06:34.760
has decided is too dangerous or threatening to bring into relationship.

06:35.160 --> 06:37.480
So for us to even be aware of internally

06:37.480 --> 06:40.840
and then be to now, how is that going to impact the relationship?

06:40.840 --> 06:44.360
Will this person reject me, punish me, whatever it is for having this feeling?

06:44.640 --> 06:47.840
So all these defensive structures and mechanisms get created.

06:47.840 --> 06:51.360
And ISTDP is really about getting very clear

06:51.360 --> 06:53.920
on what the defensive mechanisms are that are in operation,

06:54.400 --> 06:57.160
bringing that into sort of stark relief for the patient,

06:57.800 --> 07:02.080
